Dialogue: 0,0:00:01.17,0:00:04.55,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,W-What?! Legion?!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:04.55,0:00:07.88,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Then the ones that attacked \Nus are from Zentopia?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:08.18,0:00:10.63,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah. I'm positive.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:10.88,0:00:14.20,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Why would Fiore's largest religious \Norganization attack us?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:14.54,0:00:19.45,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,I don't know, but he said \Nsome crap about a crusade...
Dialogue: 0,0:00:20.45,0:00:22.74,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Who gives a damn about all that?!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:23.11,0:00:26.95,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Lucy, I swear we'll get \Nthat memento back for you!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:27.24,0:00:28.04,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:28.79,0:00:31.11,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Don't be so glum.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:31.11,0:00:34.09,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,You were being controlled by magic...
Dialogue: 0,0:00:34.09,0:00:38.11,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm sorry. I couldn't do anything to help...
Dialogue: 0,0:00:38.45,0:00:41.80,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,No, it's not your fault, Michelle.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:42.89,0:00:44.04,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,It's because...
Dialogue: 0,0:00:44.75,0:00:47.73,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,It's because... I was weak...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:24.08,0:02:28.89,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,The church attacks that happened soon \Nbefore Zentopia's anniversary event...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:29.23,0:02:32.36,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,A mysterious clock hand \Nand a sinister line...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:32.36,0:02:34.92,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,That Legion was after...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:35.32,0:02:38.42,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,...and some crusade...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:38.81,0:02:40.18,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,I don't like it.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:40.69,0:02:44.73,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,I don't like that they \Nmade light of Fairy Tail,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:44.73,0:02:46.77,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,an' I hope we don't let it just end \Nwith our asses gettin' kicked...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:46.77,0:02:49.77,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,What happened with the members \Nthat were sent in pursuit?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:49.77,0:02:52.90,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,According to Warren, all of \Nthe teams lost track of them.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:53.71,0:02:56.96,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,But it's not over. It's just begun...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:56.96,0:02:58.36,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,...I suppose you could say.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:58.36,0:03:02.57,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Now you're talkin'! Now we can look forward \Nto gettin' payback, 100 times over!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:02.57,0:03:03.79,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Right?!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:05.68,0:03:06.48,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:09.44,0:03:11.21,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Key of the Starry Heavens!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:16.09,0:03:18.16,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,The crusade they mentioned...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:18.58,0:03:22.47,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Legion is trying to \Naccomplish something big...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:23.93,0:03:27.15,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,For that, the clock hand was necessary.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:27.15,0:03:30.60,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,And the words that were inscribed on it...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:30.87,0:03:32.56,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Time is etched...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:32.56,0:03:35.70,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,and then chaos descends...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:39.03,0:03:40.61,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,What's wrong, Carla?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:40.61,0:03:43.44,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Nothing. Never mind.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:43.44,0:03:47.25,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,That clock actually exists somewhere...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:48.08,0:03:50.80,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Do they mean to use it for their crusade?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:51.17,0:03:55.54,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,"Chaos descends..." My guess it's \Na reference to that crusade.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:56.56,0:03:59.85,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Natsu, are you okay? Are you \Nfollowing the conversation?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:59.85,0:04:00.76,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, shut up!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:00.76,0:04:02.62,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Then rules are unnecessary here.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:02.62,0:04:04.28,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,That's right up my alley!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:04.28,0:04:08.97,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Listen, everything works more or less \Nbecause the world has rules, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:08.97,0:04:11.88,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Like when someone takes something \Nthat's not theirs, they're a thief?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:11.88,0:04:14.85,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Like, lock your door whenever you go out?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:14.85,0:04:19.42,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,All of our freedoms were built upon \Nthe foundations of certain rules.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:19.42,0:04:22.15,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Without them, everything \Nwould be pure lawlessness.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:22.15,0:04:24.82,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Is that what they're trying \Nto achieve with their crusade?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:25.34,0:04:28.46,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Sounds like things are gettin' crazy again...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:28.46,0:04:31.39,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,In the first place, you \Ncan't call robbing someone
Dialogue: 0,0:04:31.39,0:04:34.24,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,of their property an act of holiness.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:34.24,0:04:35.90,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,A clue...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:36.46,0:04:42.34,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Maybe Legion is looking for \Nanother part of the clock now...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:43.05,0:04:45.65,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,If we can find out what their purpose is,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:45.65,0:04:47.99,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,the meaning of the memento \Nwill also become clear.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:48.30,0:04:52.67,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,All we can do is investigate. And maybe \Nthat'll tell us where they are...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:53.10,0:04:56.06,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Or maybe they'll notice us \Nsniffing around and come for us.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:56.06,0:04:58.86,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,I like that thinkin'! Let's go!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:58.86,0:05:01.69,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,But where should we start investigating?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:01.69,0:05:03.84,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,I'll try doing a divination.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:03.84,0:05:06.32,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,That should narrow it down at least.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:06.56,0:05:09.37,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Did you hear that?! That's my daughter!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:09.37,0:05:10.69,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah, yeah...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:11.94,0:05:16.15,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,I have the update, sir! Nothing out of \Nthe ordinary at the two other parishes.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:16.15,0:05:16.94,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Good work.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:17.55,0:05:19.51,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Is it possible that another place
Dialogue: 0,0:05:19.51,0:05:21.30,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,besides the three that we \Nsupposed will come under attack?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:21.30,0:05:22.59,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,I cannot say for sure.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:22.59,0:05:26.32,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,But from the results of our investigation
Dialogue: 0,0:05:26.32,0:05:28.30,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,of the incidents up to now \Nand the latest divination...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:28.30,0:05:32.60,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,...three possibilities have been \Nderived. I have faith in that.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:32.60,0:05:33.97,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Who's inside?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:33.97,0:05:37.28,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,According to the priest, no \None is here at this hour.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:40.48,0:05:44.68,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Excited! Hot! Rich!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:44.68,0:05:46.61,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,So you're the one...?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:46.61,0:05:49.55,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Don't think I'll sit quietly \Nand let you do me in, monster!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:50.10,0:05:53.66,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Please sit quietly and let me do you in!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:55.66,0:05:56.67,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,A scream?!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:56.67,0:05:57.41,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,How can that be?!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:57.67,0:05:59.00,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, no! Hurry!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:05.91,0:06:07.64,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Well, well...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:07.64,0:06:13.38,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,The Detention Corps is working hard \Nin the wee hours of the morning...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:13.38,0:06:15.86,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Are you the one responsible \Nfor the string of attacks?!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:17.10,0:06:17.87,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,What is that?!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:17.87,0:06:18.83,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,It's huge!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:18.83,0:06:20.02,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,What the devil are you?!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:20.02,0:06:23.90,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Well, my name is Jackpot...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:23.90,0:06:25.52,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,...and so...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:27.94,0:06:30.34,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, there we go!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:30.34,0:06:31.87,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Washtubs it is!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:32.57,0:06:33.86,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Hot!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:33.86,0:06:35.64,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Totally hot!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:35.64,0:06:38.76,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,On top of that, Rushing \NDown the Path of Evil!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:39.22,0:06:44.41,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, yeah! Lightning bonus!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:45.80,0:06:48.63,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Who is this clown?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:49.40,0:06:51.21,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Let's go again!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:51.21,0:06:53.85,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Here it is! Oni Flash!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:55.83,0:06:58.04,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,This is totally hot.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:59.90,0:07:00.75,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,He disappeared!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:00.75,0:07:01.52,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,What was that?!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:01.52,0:07:03.70,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Was that the serial attacker?!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:03.70,0:07:09.06,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,So it would seem... And his jocular manner \Nmakes him all the more fearsome...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:10.11,0:07:14.16,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,So, sorry, but... can we ask you to do it?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:14.16,0:07:16.47,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Well, I don't mind...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:16.94,0:07:20.08,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,We couldn't ask anyone but you \Nto do somethin' this dangerous.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:20.08,0:07:23.46,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,We'll partner you up with \Njust the right person.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:23.46,0:07:26.49,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Look at him sneaking around again \Nin the middle of the night...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:26.49,0:07:28.25,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, don't be so hard on him.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:28.25,0:07:30.92,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Cana-chan, did you hear that?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:30.92,0:07:32.15,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,A little bit.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:32.15,0:07:33.80,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,How about going with Papa?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:33.80,0:07:36.70,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,What could be better than a \Nfather and daughter trip, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:36.70,0:07:37.98,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Why don't you go by yourself?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:41.02,0:07:43.27,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,You're always so mean to me, Cana-chan...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:43.27,0:07:44.76,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Get going!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:44.76,0:07:46.27,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,See you later!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:46.27,0:07:48.80,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Why don't you try being \Na little nicer to him?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:48.80,0:07:50.66,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,You've got to be kidding!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:51.09,0:07:55.13,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeesh... He's so cool when he \Nacts with determination, but...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:56.14,0:07:57.89,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Tonight, too?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:57.89,0:08:00.89,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,It seems his nightmares \Nbecome worse by the night...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:00.89,0:08:03.20,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,And sedatives don't work either?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:03.62,0:08:05.53,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Are you awake?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:05.53,0:08:06.79,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,How do you feel?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:08.83,0:08:11.40,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Mmm... It was that dream again..
Dialogue: 0,0:08:12.92,0:08:14.69,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Tonight as well?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:15.00,0:08:20.47,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes... It's a terribly ill-omened dream...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:20.47,0:08:23.93,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,But what is it trying to tell me?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:24.63,0:08:27.50,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Already, I am afraid to sleep.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:27.50,0:08:30.41,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,But if you don't sleep, it \Nwill affect your health.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:30.86,0:08:33.41,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,The anniversary event is also near...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:33.41,0:08:38.16,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Please summon the cardinals, just \Nin case something happens to me.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:38.42,0:08:40.35,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Don't talk like that!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:40.62,0:08:44.54,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,In order to lead the people, \Nit sometimes becomes necessary
Dialogue: 0,0:08:44.54,0:08:46.08,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,to make difficult choices.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:46.99,0:08:51.78,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,And that is the duty of the \NArchbishop of Zentopia.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:55.71,0:08:57.85,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,I kind of remember seeing this before...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:57.85,0:08:59.18,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,It's the Heartfilia mansion.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:59.45,0:09:01.10,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Was it put up for sale?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:01.10,0:09:04.38,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,It's in good shape, considering \Nseven years have passed.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:04.38,0:09:08.27,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Then it must be kept up periodically \Nuntil a buyer is found, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:08.27,0:09:13.27,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,The administrator of the estate says they \Nhaven't been able to find a buyer...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:13.27,0:09:15.11,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Probably because it's too luxurious...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:15.11,0:09:17.23,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,This brings back memories...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:17.23,0:09:20.53,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,I used to think of this \Nas a castle back then...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:20.53,0:09:22.65,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,And it hasn't changed...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:22.65,0:09:24.54,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Michelle, you've been here before?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:25.95,0:09:28.49,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,We used to play a lot together...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:28.49,0:09:32.18,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh... That's... right...?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:32.18,0:09:35.26,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Nee-san, you used to make clothes for me...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:35.26,0:09:37.54,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Right, right... I may have...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:37.54,0:09:38.91,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Clothes?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:38.91,0:09:41.09,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,She must be better with \Nher hands than I thought.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:41.09,0:09:43.22,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,That's cute.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:43.22,0:09:46.57,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Although the clothes were made with \Ncolored construction paper and flowers...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:47.40,0:09:48.73,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, jeez...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:48.73,0:09:51.73,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,How do you make clothes with \Nconstruction paper and flowers?!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:51.73,0:09:53.24,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Well, think...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:54.32,0:09:55.91,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Go home!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:57.01,0:10:01.27,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,I'd like to get to the reason \Nwe're here. Do you mind?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:01.27,0:10:02.62,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,No objections!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:02.62,0:10:05.86,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Um... Where should we start?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:05.86,0:10:08.33,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,And what are we supposed to be looking for?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:08.33,0:10:11.54,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,That's the reason I had \Nso many of us come here.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:11.86,0:10:15.67,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,We'll spread out in groups of two \Nand thoroughly search every room.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:16.61,0:10:23.22,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Look for clock parts, old clocks, anything \Nthat reminds you of those words,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:23.22,0:10:27.30,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,books that have something to do with \Nancient Potamelian, anything...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:27.54,0:10:30.95,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Examine anything that makes \Nyou think, "How about this?"
Dialogue: 0,0:10:33.06,0:10:36.15,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,There's still a lot of furniture left, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:36.15,0:10:42.63,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah. I was told that some of it is \Npriceless and some of it is just junk...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:47.72,0:10:49.21,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,What's this?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:50.05,0:10:54.17,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,I think this was done shortly \Nbefore my mom passed.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:54.54,0:10:58.76,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,I just remember being \Ntold to sit like that...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:59.23,0:11:03.74,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,It was hard on me to think \Nabout her afterwards...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:03.74,0:11:06.43,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,And I took it out on other \Npeople and things...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:06.68,0:11:09.78,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,I think I made everyone worry about me...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:10.14,0:11:11.56,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:13.36,0:11:17.44,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,I just decided! One day, I'm \Ngonna buy this house back!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:17.44,0:11:21.47,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,And then I'll restore it back to the \Nway it was, as much as possible!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:21.95,0:11:24.31,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Back to... the way it was?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:24.31,0:11:25.14,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:29.04,0:11:30.52,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Is something wrong?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:30.52,0:11:35.83,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,No. It's a lovely idea. I think \NUncle Jude would be pleased.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:36.09,0:11:38.57,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,I see... My dad...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:41.09,0:11:42.70,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,It's like a library!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:42.70,0:11:44.91,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,This is my father's study.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:44.91,0:11:48.05,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,He collected more books than me.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:48.05,0:11:49.69,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Maybe...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:49.69,0:11:52.34,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,...there's a book in here \Nthat'll give us a clue!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:53.37,0:11:55.10,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Hmm...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:55.10,0:11:58.45,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Easier said than done. \NWith this many books...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:01.03,0:12:03.10,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,"To My Daughter"...?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:03.10,0:12:04.70,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Nee-san, look at this!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:05.40,0:12:07.92,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,This is a strange book...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:15.79,0:12:18.11,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,All of the pages are blank.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:18.11,0:12:22.34,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,The title is "To My Daughter"... \Nand there's no publication data.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:22.60,0:12:25.82,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Then there's some magic \Nat work on the book...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:25.82,0:12:27.30,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,By the way, Nee-san...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:29.02,0:12:30.32,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Is he sleeping?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:30.32,0:12:32.48,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,No, he's tuning in.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:32.96,0:12:35.85,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Old Master Crux should be \Nable to learn something.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:36.23,0:12:38.64,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Diao!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:39.11,0:12:40.12,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Well?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:40.12,0:12:44.44,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Indeed, this is decidedly nothing \Nmore than an old bundle of paper.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:44.44,0:12:47.87,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,There's no magic involved, let alone \Ncharacters written in invisible ink.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:47.87,0:12:52.12,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Furthermore, your father bound \Nthese pages together himself.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:52.12,0:12:55.58,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,I see... Did you learn anything else?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:55.58,0:12:57.33,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,There is one more thing.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:57.33,0:12:59.72,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,From ancient times, there \Nhave been certain "rules"
Dialogue: 0,0:12:59.72,0:13:01.86,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,when it comes to this \Nparticular type of riddle.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:01.86,0:13:04.73,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,For example, this title...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:04.73,0:13:07.20,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,What if it's an anagram?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:07.20,0:13:08.36,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,I see!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:08.36,0:13:10.76,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,So we try putting the letters \Nin a different order, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:12.34,0:13:15.39,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,I wouldn't know a potential \Nclue if it bit me in the ass!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:15.39,0:13:17.43,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm hungry...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:17.98,0:13:20.27,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,What are you guys playin' a game for?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:20.27,0:13:21.70,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Natsu-san!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:21.70,0:13:22.81,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Keep your silence.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:22.81,0:13:24.55,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,We're thinking!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:24.55,0:13:26.28,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,What's that? A puzzle?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:26.28,0:13:28.25,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,We're trying to decipher an anagram.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:28.25,0:13:30.50,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Anagra...? Oh, that.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:30.50,0:13:32.24,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Well, it is like a puzzle.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:32.49,0:13:35.65,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Huh, that looks like fun! Let me...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:37.46,0:13:39.49,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,What do you think you're doing?!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:39.49,0:13:41.10,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,We were trying to think!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:41.10,0:13:42.70,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Oops.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:43.80,0:13:46.13,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,We were on the verge of getting \Na flash of inspiration!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:46.13,0:13:48.55,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Erza-san is serious...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:48.55,0:13:51.63,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,She's the type that really \Nfocuses on this kind of thing.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:51.63,0:13:54.37,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Jeez! You scattered the \Ncards all over the place...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:54.37,0:13:56.93,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Ah... Is this...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:57.35,0:13:59.60,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Diao!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:59.60,0:14:02.29,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Those four letters... "Myth", correct?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:02.29,0:14:03.20,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,"Myth"?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:03.20,0:14:04.32,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Indeed.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:04.32,0:14:06.56,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Like an old legend...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:06.56,0:14:08.20,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,I think we're gettin' there.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:08.71,0:14:10.81,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,What can we do with the remaining letters?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:11.20,0:14:14.87,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Duo... Great... Myth...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:14.87,0:14:19.65,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,That's it! There are two books \Nreferred to as "The Two Great Myths"!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:19.65,0:14:21.29,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,The author is Will Neville.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:21.29,0:14:26.55,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,One book is titled "Life of the Clockwork" \Nand it's got those words in it!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:26.55,0:14:29.45,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Is that the book you had \Nin your room, Nee-san?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:29.45,0:14:31.65,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Uh-huh. What a coincidence!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:31.65,0:14:33.55,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,As for the other myth...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:33.55,0:14:36.83,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Ta-daa! It's called "Key \Nof the Starry Heavens"!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:36.83,0:14:38.68,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Isn't that a picture book?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:38.68,0:14:42.60,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,It's not just any old picture \Nbook! It's really magical...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:42.60,0:14:46.15,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,At any rate, doesn't the \Nword "key" strike you?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:46.15,0:14:50.88,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah. Maybe there's some kind \Nof hint inside the book.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:51.32,0:14:55.97,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Like another anagram? I guess \Nit wouldn't be that easy...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:55.97,0:14:58.77,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,But if we look at it from another way, \Nwe may be able to learn something...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:59.85,0:15:00.71,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,No...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:01.37,0:15:02.67,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Carla?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:02.67,0:15:05.96,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,I don't know if it has to \Ndo with that clock hand...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:05.96,0:15:09.83,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,...but maybe there's a message \Nfrom my father in this book!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:10.34,0:15:14.05,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,And what is that kitty-cat \Nover there holding?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:14.05,0:15:16.37,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,A book about a rabbit and a turtle.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:16.37,0:15:19.99,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,I think this book is really magical, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:19.99,0:15:22.31,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Would you give me that book?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:22.55,0:15:24.95,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,You're after this book?!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:25.56,0:15:28.28,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,That's not really a funny joke.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:30.20,0:15:31.78,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,W-What the hell is that?!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:31.78,0:15:33.20,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,The door handle expanded!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:33.20,0:15:35.69,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,You've got a rather limited \Npower of expression, it seems.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:35.69,0:15:40.29,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,You couldn't say the door handle doubled \Nin size, which broke down the door?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:40.29,0:15:42.22,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,I don't believe it! He's...?!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:42.22,0:15:43.42,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,You mean...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:43.42,0:15:48.75,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,An Exceed! But was this guy in Extalia?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:49.07,0:15:55.07,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,No... I bet he was sent to this world \Nat the same time we were, Happy!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:55.07,0:15:57.19,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Why, you... Who the hell are you?!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:57.19,0:15:59.03,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,I am the head of Legion...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:59.03,0:16:00.20,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Samuel.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:00.85,0:16:03.50,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,So you sniffed us out right \Naway and came runnin', huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:03.50,0:16:05.43,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Then give us back the clock hand!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:05.43,0:16:06.11,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Never.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:06.11,0:16:07.02,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,What?!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:07.60,0:16:12.69,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Anyway, you've done exactly as I predicted.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:12.69,0:16:15.13,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,I knew you would come here.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:15.13,0:16:17.11,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,And that you would find a clue.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:17.11,0:16:18.57,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,As indeed, you have.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:18.57,0:16:19.87,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm a genius.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:19.87,0:16:21.87,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,That guy's gettin' on my nerves...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:21.87,0:16:24.20,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,We'll have to attack before \Nhe gets the chance...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:24.20,0:16:25.04,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Erza-san!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:25.04,0:16:25.61,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Right.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:27.29,0:16:29.84,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Ice Make: Lance!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:30.46,0:16:31.88,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Victory goes to the one \Nwho makes the first move!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:31.94,0:16:34.22,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Roar of the Fire Dragon!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:39.81,0:16:41.06,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Wait a...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:42.60,0:16:43.63,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,No!!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:43.63,0:16:45.16,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,What are you doing?!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:45.16,0:16:48.73,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,I just decided to buy this house back!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:48.73,0:16:51.80,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Hold it! That guy repelled our magic!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:51.80,0:16:54.11,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm the spearhead of Legion...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:54.36,0:16:57.99,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Dan Straight is here!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:57.99,0:16:59.64,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Another weirdo...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:59.64,0:17:01.66,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Did you get a good look \Nat the power of my shield?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:01.66,0:17:04.04,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Magic shield "Ricochet"!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:04.04,0:17:07.21,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,It blocks any and all attacks, \Nthen scatters them about!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:07.21,0:17:10.12,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Ricochet... So everything \Nbounces off of it...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:10.12,0:17:12.12,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Then we can't just attack willy-nilly...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:12.12,0:17:15.31,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,One false move and Lucy will be \Nbuying back a mountain of debris!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:15.31,0:17:17.13,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,We got one pain in the ass \Ncomin' in after another!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:17.38,0:17:18.43,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,They're going to attack.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:18.43,0:17:20.63,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,No matter how many times they \Nattack, nothing will change!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:20.63,0:17:23.02,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,I'll destroy that thing before \Nit can repel my attack!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:26.64,0:17:28.52,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,I told you to stop it!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:28.52,0:17:31.19,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Dan, that girl has the book.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:31.61,0:17:32.87,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Lucy-san!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:32.87,0:17:34.68,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,I'll lure that guy outside!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:34.68,0:17:36.11,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,No! It's too dangerous, Nee-san!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:36.11,0:17:39.93,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Here's the book! Steal it if you can!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:45.83,0:17:48.08,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Th-Throb!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:49.00,0:17:50.41,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,You're beautiful!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:50.41,0:17:52.22,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Throb!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:52.22,0:17:55.36,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Beautiful! This wizard is too beautiful!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:55.36,0:17:58.42,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,She's shot me right through the heart!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:58.42,0:18:02.22,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,I can't stand it! I can't \Nstand it! She's crushed me!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:02.22,0:18:03.98,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,By the way, what's your name?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:03.98,0:18:05.07,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Lucy...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:05.07,0:18:07.56,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Lucy! I can't stand it!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:07.83,0:18:09.85,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Lu! Cy!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:09.85,0:18:12.90,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,You've touched me to the quick!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:13.14,0:18:17.42,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Can I call you Lu-tan? \NLu-chan? Lu-pi? Lun-lun?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:17.42,0:18:18.33,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Whatever...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:18.33,0:18:19.40,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,It's begun...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:19.40,0:18:21.57,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,"Whatever"!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:21.57,0:18:23.43,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,That voice! Those eyes!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:23.43,0:18:25.37,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,That mouth! That hair!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:25.37,0:18:26.87,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,That chest! That waist!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:26.87,0:18:27.81,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Those legs!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:27.81,0:18:33.59,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,All of it makes my Fibonacci \Nsequence chirp! It spells out...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:33.59,0:18:34.33,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,L!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:34.33,0:18:34.88,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,O!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:34.88,0:18:35.67,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,V!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:35.67,0:18:36.59,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,E!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:36.59,0:18:38.16,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,That's love!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:38.16,0:18:39.73,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,W-What are you talking about?!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:39.73,0:18:40.89,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Love!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:41.55,0:18:42.18,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Lucy!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:42.18,0:18:43.47,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Lucy!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:44.43,0:18:47.96,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Cut it out! Don't butt in!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:48.75,0:18:52.69,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Go, Lucy and Michelle. We \Ncan't let them take that book!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:52.69,0:18:54.10,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,R-Right!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:54.10,0:18:57.54,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Everyone, I need you on \Nsupport. Leave this to me!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:57.54,0:18:59.64,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,I-I think we were overwhelmed by that...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:59.64,0:19:01.28,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Our brains were at a standstill...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:01.28,0:19:04.03,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Huh. You've got a lot of \Nconfidence in yourself.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:04.03,0:19:05.66,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,You'd do well not to underestimate us.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:05.66,0:19:07.48,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Let me hit 'em, too!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:07.48,0:19:09.37,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,You protect Lucy!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:09.75,0:19:10.87,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Run, Lucy!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:10.87,0:19:11.91,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Let's go!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:11.91,0:19:12.76,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Right!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:12.76,0:19:15.25,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm not done talking to you!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:17.96,0:19:20.32,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Don't destroy the house!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:22.53,0:19:23.18,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Hmph.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:23.67,0:19:28.06,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Alright. Certainly, the \Nframework of this building...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:28.56,0:19:31.35,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Dan, I'll leave Titania to you.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:31.35,0:19:32.31,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:32.31,0:19:33.40,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Come on, then!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:36.22,0:19:38.40,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Even physical attacks bounce off?!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:38.40,0:19:39.31,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Alrighty!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:42.04,0:19:43.28,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,What?!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:49.74,0:19:51.91,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,What kind of magic is this?!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:52.30,0:19:54.31,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,I heard you scream.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:54.31,0:19:58.08,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,You're pretty cute yourself, \Nbut the difference between
Dialogue: 0,0:19:58.08,0:20:00.85,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,you and Lu-tan is greater \Nthan the width of an ocean!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:00.85,0:20:02.61,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,What's your deal, jackass?!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:02.61,0:20:06.89,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Our time is about up. See you again, Titania!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:07.80,0:20:10.30,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey! Wait a second!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:11.49,0:20:12.44,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,What was that?!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:12.44,0:20:14.01,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,It was from the study!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:14.01,0:20:15.02,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Erza!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:15.02,0:20:16.73,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Nee-san, we have to hurry!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:16.73,0:20:18.46,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,R-Right...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:20.32,0:20:21.88,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,When did he...?!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:21.88,0:20:25.94,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Just as I predicted. The \Nanswer came forth simply,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:25.94,0:20:29.85,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,based on your mental state and \Nthe structure of this abode.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:29.85,0:20:33.07,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,No one wants to hear your mumbling!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:33.50,0:20:34.34,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Natsu!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:34.34,0:20:35.46,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Natsu-san!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:35.46,0:20:36.20,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Bastard!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:36.20,0:20:37.50,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,How dare you do that to Natsu-san?!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:40.69,0:20:42.30,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Exactly as planned...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:43.70,0:20:45.38,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Natsu!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:45.38,0:20:47.72,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Are you okay?!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:45.70,0:20:47.40,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Son of a bitch!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:47.72,0:20:49.35,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Wait a second!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:53.68,0:20:55.31,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Happy! Where's Natsu?!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:55.31,0:20:56.36,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Is he alright?!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:56.36,0:20:58.97,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,I stepped on him.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:58.97,0:21:00.15,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,He's tiny!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:00.15,0:21:03.65,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Now, why don't you stop running around?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:03.65,0:21:05.36,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,What did you do to Natsu?!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:05.36,0:21:08.04,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm able to change the size \Nof anything I touch...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:08.37,0:21:12.39,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,...with my magic spear! That's \Nthe power of "Happy Lucky"!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:12.39,0:21:16.17,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,So, would you hand over that \Nbook without any more fuss?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:16.17,0:21:19.39,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,I don't like to do things Mary's way.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:19.39,0:21:22.36,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,I would prefer to avoid having \Nto get even rougher on you.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:22.36,0:21:23.09,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,What?!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:23.35,0:21:24.38,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Happy!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:24.38,0:21:26.04,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Get the book and escape!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:26.04,0:21:27.76,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Aye, sir!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:28.72,0:21:31.09,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey! Get back here!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:31.09,0:21:33.01,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Go! Go!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:33.01,0:21:34.75,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Not clever by half...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:36.06,0:21:37.60,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,The book is right here.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:37.60,0:21:38.55,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:38.55,0:21:40.08,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,He figured it out right away!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:40.08,0:21:41.25,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,How?!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:41.25,0:21:45.83,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Everything is cause and effect. \NI can read the calculations.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:45.83,0:21:49.86,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,That's why I can see through \Neverything that you people do.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:52.62,0:21:56.34,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,You can have the book back. \NI memorized its contents.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:56.34,0:21:57.44,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:59.65,0:22:02.06,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,'Til we meet again, Lu-tan!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:02.06,0:22:04.43,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Next time, let's go on a \Ndate, just the two of us!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:04.43,0:22:07.09,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Dan... Have you gained weight again?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:07.09,0:22:09.09,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,He left the book here...
Dialogue: 0,0:22:09.09,0:22:10.94,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Meaning he doesn't see \Nus as any kind of threat.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:10.94,0:22:12.29,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Condescending bastard...
Dialogue: 0,0:22:12.29,0:22:14.19,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,I swear I'll get them back...
Dialogue: 0,0:22:14.19,0:22:16.78,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Turn me back to normal!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:15.07,0:22:16.78,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Turn him back!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:17.03,0:22:18.42,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Dad...
Dialogue: 0,0:22:19.18,0:22:21.68,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,What are you trying to tell me?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:55.26,0:23:58.10,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,What am I gonna do about this body?!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:58.10,0:24:00.38,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Natsu, you're gonna be dead \Nweight this time around.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:00.38,0:24:01.38,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,What's that?!
Dialogue: 0,0:24:01.38,0:24:05.21,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,After all, at that size, you can't put \Nout much more fire than a candle, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:24:05.21,0:24:09.43,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Hmph! If I put my mind to it, \NI can even barbecue underwater!
Dialogue: 0,0:24:09.43,0:24:11.82,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Even when you threaten, \Nit just comes off as cute!
Dialogue: 0,0:24:11.82,0:24:14.06,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Happy, you're gonna get it...
Dialogue: 0,0:24:14.06,0:24:16.39,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Next time: Traveling Companions!
Dialogue: 0,0:24:16.39,0:24:19.14,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Huh? Natsu, are you angry?
Dialogue: 0,0:24:19.14,0:24:20.66,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Of course I am!
Dialogue: 0,0:24:20.66,0:24:22.85,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Even an angry Natsu is cute...
